
[1]stillness

   STILLNESS, n.

   1. Freedom from noise or motion; calmness; quiet; silence; as the
   stillness of the night, the air or the sea.

   2. Freedom from agitation or excitement; as the stillness of the
   passions.

   3. Habitual silence; taciturnity.

   The gravity and stillness of your youth, the world hath noted.
